        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 6:48PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 648 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles west of Acoma Pueblo, or 25 miles south of Grants, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grants, McCartys, Skyline-Ganipa, San Fidel, Cubero, San Rafael in
Cibola County, Acomita Lake, Acomita, North Acomita Village and
Seama.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 82 and 104.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Accumulations of small hail on roads can create very slick and
hazardous driving conditions.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
